## M4.5a: shadow must be looked up reverse-order in the checker.
##
## `x =! 1` makes the OLD `x` immutable. `new x = 2` introduces a fresh,
## mutable `x`. `x = 3` reassigns the NEW `x` (legal). With the
## insertion-order lookup bug, the checker finds the OLD fixed `x` and
## rejects this with "cannot reassign fixed binding".
##
## EXPECTED: clean (no diagnostics).

sub main()
  x =! 1
  new x = 2
  x = 3
